01:01:14,904 --> 01:01:16,895
- Is it really your turn?

1090
01:01:16,939 --> 01:01:18,497
- I'm not a liar.

1091
01:01:24,747 --> 01:01:26,078
Ta-da.

1092
01:01:26,115 --> 01:01:28,242
See?
It's a perfect number.

1093
01:01:28,284 --> 01:01:29,342
- Awesome!

1094
01:01:29,385 --> 01:01:30,875
- Where did you get that?

1095
01:01:30,920 --> 01:01:32,353
- I made it.

1096
01:01:32,388 --> 01:01:35,186
42 plus 5 equals 48.

1097
01:01:35,224 --> 01:01:38,057
- No, it's not.
It's 47.

1098
01:01:39,662 --> 01:01:41,653
- You didn't make it.

1099
01:01:41,698 --> 01:01:44,360
I know who it belongs to.

1100
01:01:44,400 --> 01:01:46,595
- It's mine, and I made it.

1101
01:01:47,904 --> 01:01:50,896
[bell ringing]

1102
01:01:54,444 --> 01:01:57,174
[children chattering]

1103
01:01:57,213 --> 01:01:58,680
- Go on, Lisa.

1104
01:01:58,715 --> 01:02:02,207
- Okay, but don't let her
get away with anything.

1105
01:02:06,189 --> 01:02:11,354
- So how about you and I go
to the hardware store together

1106
01:02:11,394 --> 01:02:15,524
and we'll give the number back
to Mr. Jones?

1107
01:02:15,565 --> 01:02:19,331
I mean, he'll be so happy
that he got his number back,

1108
01:02:19,368 --> 01:02:21,063
he may even give you a reward.

1109
01:02:21,104 --> 01:02:23,004
- A reward?

1110
01:02:23,039 --> 01:02:25,701
I don't want a stupid reward.

1111
01:02:25,742 --> 01:02:28,267
And you cannot keep me
from recess.

1112
01:02:28,311 --> 01:02:31,474
- Give...it...to me.

1113
01:02:40,389 --> 01:02:42,414
- Weirdo.

1114
01:02:48,765 --> 01:02:49,789
- I'll go.

1115
01:02:52,835 --> 01:02:55,804
I'll go to the hardware store
with you.

1116
01:02:55,838 --> 01:02:59,239
Then you can take me
to visit my mom.

1117
01:03:03,012 --> 01:03:04,604
- Hey, you psyched

1118
01:03:04,647 --> 01:03:06,615
for the sulfuric acid experiment
tomorrow?

1119
01:03:06,649 --> 01:03:08,310
We're gonna rock that.

1120
01:03:11,854 --> 01:03:13,515
- Mr. Smith.

1121
01:03:13,556 --> 01:03:15,421
- What's up?

1122
01:03:15,458 --> 01:03:17,255
- Want to come
to the hardware store

1123
01:03:17,293 --> 01:03:18,624
with me and Miss Gray?

1124
01:03:18,661 --> 01:03:19,821
- I can't.

1125
01:03:19,862 --> 01:03:21,625
I have my after-school
science club meeting.

1126
01:03:21,664 --> 01:03:24,292
I have to show up
because I said I would,

1127
01:03:24,333 --> 01:03:26,563
and I always mean what I say
and say what I mean.

1128
01:03:26,602 --> 01:03:27,864
I'm a straight shooter.

1129
01:03:27,904 --> 01:03:29,531
Not everyone is, but...

1130
01:03:29,572 --> 01:03:31,437
Hey, listen,
thanks for the invite.

1131
01:03:31,474 --> 01:03:34,534
- You're gonna miss a good time.

1132
01:03:38,748 --> 01:03:41,308
- Mr. Jones?

1133
01:03:42,418 --> 01:03:44,443
- Mr. Jones?

1134
01:03:51,060 --> 01:03:52,960
Mr. Jones?

1135
01:03:56,098 --> 01:03:58,931
If he's not here, why would he
leave his door open?

1136
01:03:58,968 --> 01:04:02,028
- Maybe he was captured
by pirates.

1137
01:04:14,383 --> 01:04:15,782
This way.

1138
01:04:19,822 --> 01:04:22,256
- "And falling on a bench,
he laughed until the tears..."

1139
01:04:22,291 --> 01:04:23,781
- Mom!
Nan!

1140
01:04:23,826 --> 01:04:25,157
- Hi.

1141
01:04:33,202 --> 01:04:37,935
- This is my math teacher,
Miss Gray.

1142
01:04:37,974 --> 01:04:41,375
- Is she an invisible
math teacher?

1143
01:04:42,411 --> 01:04:43,844
- Miss Gray?

1144
01:04:49,085 --> 01:04:53,181
This is Miss Gray.

1145
01:04:54,457 --> 01:04:56,118
- Lisa, you want to get
some potato chips?

1146
01:04:56,158 --> 01:04:57,284
- Aye-aye, matey.

1147
01:04:57,326 --> 01:04:58,554
- Arr!
Shiver me timbers.

1148
01:04:58,594 --> 01:04:59,583
Well, come on.

1149
01:04:59,629 --> 01:05:02,189
- [giggling]

1150
01:05:09,105 --> 01:05:11,266
- I really like your hair.

1151
01:05:11,307 --> 01:05:13,502
- [chuckles softly]

1152
01:05:17,446 --> 01:05:20,415
You can't catch cancer.

1153
01:05:30,726 --> 01:05:35,095
- Lisa asked me
to bring her here today.

1154
01:05:37,600 --> 01:05:40,592
- Yeah, she doesn't
like my sister very much.

1155
01:05:44,073 --> 01:05:47,338
But she likes you.

1156
01:05:47,376 --> 01:05:49,640
- I like her too.

1157
01:05:57,753 --> 01:06:02,747
Her dad got her into pirates,
she said.

1158
01:06:05,227 --> 01:06:07,286
- No.

1159
01:06:07,330 --> 01:06:10,128
Lisa never knew her father.

1160
01:06:12,134 --> 01:06:13,567
- Well, l--I thought--

1161
01:06:13,602 --> 01:06:15,797
- Would you...

1162
01:06:15,838 --> 01:06:18,568
look in on Lisa
from time to time?

1163
01:06:26,649 --> 01:06:29,550
- Of course.

1164
01:06:54,510 --> 01:06:57,138
[doorbell ringing]

1165
01:06:57,179 --> 01:07:00,171
[frantic knocking]

1166
01:07:01,984 --> 01:07:03,576
Mr. Jones!

1167
01:07:05,488 --> 01:07:07,388
Mom?

1168
01:07:07,423 --> 01:07:08,481
Mom?
Dad?

1169
01:07:08,524 --> 01:07:10,014
Have you seen Mr. Jones?

1170
01:07:10,059 --> 01:07:11,720
Mom, have you seen Mr. Jones?

1171
01:07:11,761 --> 01:07:13,661
- He's gone.

1172
01:07:13,696 --> 01:07:16,665
And I can't find my car keys.

1173
01:07:16,699 --> 01:07:18,166
- Who's gone?
Mr. Jones?

1174
01:07:18,200 --> 01:07:21,192
- No, Mona.
Your dad.

1175
01:07:21,237 --> 01:07:23,330
Your dad's gone.

1176
01:07:23,372 --> 01:07:25,738
- What?
Where did he go?

1177
01:07:25,775 --> 01:07:26,833
- I don't know where.

1178
01:07:26,876 --> 01:07:28,503
I don't know where he is.

1179
01:07:32,815 --> 01:07:37,514
And I found these
behind the washing machine.

1180
01:07:37,553 --> 01:07:39,248
He's been hiding them,

1181
01:07:39,288 --> 01:07:42,052
and I don't know for how long
he's not taking them.

1182
01:07:44,527 --> 01:07:47,758
- This never would have happened
if I still lived here.

1183
01:07:47,797 --> 01:07:49,059
- Stop it!

1184
01:07:49,098 --> 01:07:52,465
You can't help him!

1185
01:07:52,501 --> 01:07:54,696
And I don't know
where he is.

1186
01:08:06,015 --> 01:08:07,505
- Dad?
- Is that your father?

1187
01:08:07,550 --> 01:08:08,847
I've been trying
to get him to move,

1188
01:08:08,884 --> 01:08:10,215
but he won't get up.

1189
01:08:10,252 --> 01:08:11,685
- Dad.

1190
01:08:11,720 --> 01:08:17,158
- The energy
is trapped in this circle,

1191
01:08:17,193 --> 01:08:19,252
and it needs to be released.

1192
01:08:23,365 --> 01:08:24,855
- Let's go home.

1193
01:08:24,900 --> 01:08:27,300
- Do you need me
to make a call for you?

1194
01:08:27,336 --> 01:08:30,567
- No, we're fine.
Thank you.

1195
01:08:33,809 --> 01:08:37,040
Why did you stop
taking your medicine?

1196
01:08:37,079 --> 01:08:39,673
- Because they're poison.

1197
01:08:39,715 --> 01:08:42,513
And they'll poison my body.

1198
01:08:42,551 --> 01:08:44,519
- No, it'll help you.

1199
01:08:48,657 --> 01:08:51,251
- You understand?

1200
01:08:51,293 --> 01:08:53,454
I have to dig right here.

1201
01:08:57,500 --> 01:08:59,934
If I don't open this...

1202
01:09:04,340 --> 01:09:06,865
I--

1203
01:09:06,909 --> 01:09:08,774
- Please...

1204
01:09:12,715 --> 01:09:14,512
Let's just go home.

1205
01:09:17,219 --> 01:09:19,653
- Don't you want me
to get better?

1206
01:09:19,688 --> 01:09:22,213
- That's all I want.

1207
01:09:36,205 --> 01:09:39,197
[knocking]

1208
01:09:48,050 --> 01:09:51,042
[children chattering]

1209
01:10:08,704 --> 01:10:10,672
- I have my
"numbers and materials."

1210
01:10:10,706 --> 01:10:13,800
I know it's not Friday,
but this one's special.

1211
01:10:17,580 --> 01:10:19,377
It's my dad's fake arm.

1212
01:10:19,415 --> 01:10:20,404
- Cool!

1213
01:10:20,449 --> 01:10:22,212
- It looks like a number 1,
right?

1214
01:10:22,251 --> 01:10:24,685
- Can I touch it?

1215
01:10:24,720 --> 01:10:26,813
- Pretty awesome, huh?

1216
01:10:26,855 --> 01:10:29,380
- It doesn't look like a 1.

1217
01:10:29,425 --> 01:10:30,392
It looks like an arm.

1218
01:10:30,426 --> 01:10:33,020
- It does too
look like a number 1.

1219
01:10:33,062 --> 01:10:36,520
[children chattering]

1220
01:10:36,565 --> 01:10:38,931
- Why did your dad's arm
fall off?

1221
01:10:38,968 --> 01:10:42,734
- It didn't fall off.
It got blown off in the war.

1222
01:10:42,771 --> 01:10:44,238
Should I subtract now,
Miss Gray?

1223
01:10:44,273 --> 01:10:46,036
Miss Gray?
Miss Gray.

1224
01:10:46,075 --> 01:10:47,167
Miss Gray.

1225
01:10:47,209 --> 01:10:48,198
- What?

1226
01:10:48,244 --> 01:10:49,233
- Should I subtract now?

1227
01:10:49,278 --> 01:10:50,609
Hey, that's my dad's!

1228
01:10:50,646 --> 01:10:51,635
- Elmer!

1229
01:10:51,680 --> 01:10:53,978
- Give it back!
[laughter]

1230
01:10:54,016 --> 01:10:55,745
- Get back here!

1231
01:10:55,784 --> 01:10:57,843
- Elmer, give Danny back
his dad's arm.

1232
01:10:57,886 --> 01:10:59,251
- Give it back right now!

1233
01:10:59,288 --> 01:11:01,153
- Elmer!

1234
01:11:01,190 --> 01:11:03,249
Hey, Elmer!

1235
01:11:03,292 --> 01:11:04,418
Give it!

1236
01:11:04,460 --> 01:11:05,586
Elmer, give it back!

1237
01:11:05,628 --> 01:11:08,119
- Give it back!

1238
01:11:08,163 --> 01:11:11,030
- Miss Gray,
you can't control the class.

1239
01:11:11,066 --> 01:11:12,533
You're gonna get fired.

1240
01:11:12,568 --> 01:11:14,365
- Shut up.

1241
01:11:14,403 --> 01:11:17,429
- No one cares about you, Lisa.

1242
01:11:17,473 --> 01:11:18,963
- Give me the arm!
- No!

1243
01:11:19,008 --> 01:11:20,942
- Help!

1244
01:11:20,976 --> 01:11:23,945
[laughter]

1245
01:11:23,979 --> 01:11:26,948
- Miss Gray, look!

1246
01:11:26,982 --> 01:11:27,971
[children gasp]

1247
01:11:30,686 --> 01:11:31,846
- I'm gonna divide you,

1248
01:11:31,887 --> 01:11:34,378
subtract you,
and multiply you.

1249
01:11:34,423 --> 01:11:36,357
- Lisa!

1250
01:11:36,392 --> 01:11:38,917
Go stand by the door.

1251
01:11:38,961 --> 01:11:40,087
- Ha!

1252
01:11:40,129 --> 01:11:42,427
- Ann, you need to learn
how to be nice!

1253
01:11:42,464 --> 01:11:45,490
- [whimpering]
Oh, my God.

1254
01:11:49,138 --> 01:11:51,766
- l, uh...

1255
01:11:51,807 --> 01:11:54,275
Okay.

1256
01:11:54,310 --> 01:11:56,278
I'm sorry.

1257
01:11:56,312 --> 01:11:57,643
I--

1258
01:11:57,680 --> 01:11:59,477
[sighs]

1259
01:12:02,051 --> 01:12:03,143
[loud thud, glass shatters]

1260
01:12:03,185 --> 01:12:04,675
[children shouting]

1261
01:12:04,720 --> 01:12:06,711
- Lisa! Lisa!

1262
01:12:06,755 --> 01:12:08,279
Lisa. Lisa.

1263
01:12:08,324 --> 01:12:10,451
- Let me go.
- Stop it.

1264
01:12:10,492 --> 01:12:12,858
- Let me go!
- Stop!

1265
01:12:14,063 --> 01:12:15,758
- [crying]
My mom died.

1266
01:12:15,798 --> 01:12:18,631
She died!

1267
01:12:22,137 --> 01:12:25,300
Why can't I get cancer too?

1268
01:12:29,178 --> 01:12:30,406
- I'm sorry.

1269
01:12:30,446 --> 01:12:32,710
- I'm sick of Lisa showing off.

1270
01:12:35,384 --> 01:12:36,408
- Ann!

1271
01:12:36,452 --> 01:12:38,682
- I'm gonna chop her
into pieces.

1272
01:12:38,721 --> 01:12:39,847
[sobbing]

1273
01:12:39,888 --> 01:12:41,583
- Ann...

1274
01:12:41,623 --> 01:12:43,386
put the ax down.

1275
01:12:43,425 --> 01:12:44,858
- I'm gonna chop her!

1276
01:12:44,893 --> 01:12:45,917
- No, you're not.

1277
01:12:45,961 --> 01:12:48,725
- I'm gonna chop her
into pieces.

1278
01:12:48,764 --> 01:12:51,164
- You're not gonna chop anyone.

1279
01:12:51,200 --> 01:12:52,724
- I'm sick of her.

1280
01:12:52,768 --> 01:12:53,792
- Please?

1281
01:12:53,836 --> 01:12:56,134
- And I'm sick of you.

1282
01:12:56,171 --> 01:12:57,536
- Give me the ax.

1283
01:13:05,013 --> 01:13:08,574
There comes a moment
when you look around,

1284
01:13:08,617 --> 01:13:12,576
waiting for the person in charge
to help you,

1285
01:13:12,621 --> 01:13:17,820
and then you realize
you're the person in charge.

1286
01:13:17,860 --> 01:13:20,294
You are the grown-up.

1287
01:13:22,064 --> 01:13:24,624
You're the only grown-up there.

1288
01:13:28,637 --> 01:13:29,968
And you're not very good at it.

1289
01:13:33,709 --> 01:13:38,043
Life is much, much harder
than math.

1290
01:13:40,849 --> 01:13:42,407
Dad!

1291
01:13:56,698 --> 01:13:59,690
[children screaming]

1292
01:14:00,736 --> 01:14:02,135
- Miss Gray!

1293
01:14:02,171 --> 01:14:05,572
[children screaming
and shouting]

1294
01:14:05,607 --> 01:14:08,599
[shouting fades]

1295
01:14:55,090 --> 01:14:57,217
- I got nine stitches.

1296
01:14:57,259 --> 01:14:59,227
- I got 27.

1297
01:14:59,261 --> 01:15:02,560
- 9 times 3 equals 27.

1298
01:15:02,598 --> 01:15:04,225
- You're correct.

1299
01:15:11,139 --> 01:15:14,131
[knocking]

1300
01:15:15,878 --> 01:15:17,607
- What are you doing?

1301
01:15:17,646 --> 01:15:19,170
- I'm doing what you do.

1302
01:15:19,214 --> 01:15:21,808
[knocking]

1303
01:15:21,850 --> 01:15:25,911
I used to imitate you at lunch.

1304
01:15:25,954 --> 01:15:28,718
The bench makes the same sound
as your desk.

1305
01:15:31,860 --> 01:15:35,853
Why do you do it?

1306
01:15:35,898 --> 01:15:38,731
- Why?
Um...

1307
01:15:39,801 --> 01:15:45,364
I do it when I feel...

1308
01:15:48,043 --> 01:15:49,908
Alone.

1309
01:15:49,945 --> 01:15:53,278
- Then that's why I do it.

1310
01:15:53,315 --> 01:15:55,112
I want to be like you.

1311
01:15:57,419 --> 01:15:59,353
- Don't do that.

1312
01:15:59,388 --> 01:16:03,381
Don't be like me.

1313
01:16:03,425 --> 01:16:06,189
- But I'm alone.

1314
01:16:08,964 --> 01:16:11,626
I'm all alone.

1315
01:16:36,458 --> 01:16:42,260
- Not only did you bring an ax
to school,

1316
01:16:42,297 --> 01:16:46,757
but you lied about having
a college degree.

1317
01:16:46,802 --> 01:16:49,236
Shame on you.

1318
01:16:53,508 --> 01:16:57,000
You're a wonderful math teacher,
Miss Gray.

1319
01:16:57,045 --> 01:17:00,811
But you are never allowed
to step foot in my school

1320
01:17:00,849 --> 01:17:03,113
ever again.

1321
01:17:24,039 --> 01:17:27,167
[doorbell ringing]

1322
01:17:27,209 --> 01:17:30,303
- Mr. Jones!

1323
01:17:41,857 --> 01:17:43,188
Ow!

1324
01:18:01,309 --> 01:18:03,300
Hello?
[woman shrieks]

1325
01:18:06,548 --> 01:18:08,948
- What are you doing?

1326
01:18:08,984 --> 01:18:10,178
- What are you doing?

1327
01:18:10,218 --> 01:18:13,085
Get out of here!

1328
01:18:13,121 --> 01:18:14,918
- You're not dead?

1329
01:18:14,956 --> 01:18:16,253
- Why would I be dead?

1330
01:18:16,291 --> 01:18:17,656
- What's going on?
- I don't know.

1331
01:18:17,693 --> 01:18:20,321
- I found your numbers
all over town,

1332
01:18:20,362 --> 01:18:21,954
and your store was left open.

1333
01:18:21,997 --> 01:18:23,259
Your car's gone--

1334
01:18:23,298 --> 01:18:24,663
- Get out of my bedroom.

1335
01:18:24,700 --> 01:18:26,167
- Who is this girl?

1336
01:18:26,201 --> 01:18:27,225
- Mona Gray.

1337
01:18:27,269 --> 01:18:29,567
- Mona Gray,
will you please get out?

1338
01:18:29,604 --> 01:18:31,902
- Should I call the police?
- No.

1339
01:18:31,940 --> 01:18:34,807
- But you need your numbers.

1340
01:18:34,843 --> 01:18:36,071
How are you gonna know

1341
01:18:36,111 --> 01:18:37,874
how you feel or who you are
without them?

1342
01:18:37,913 --> 01:18:40,541
- Andrea, I'll be right back.

1343
01:18:40,582 --> 01:18:41,571
I'm sorry.

1344
01:18:46,088 --> 01:18:49,922
- So why don't you need
your numbers anymore?

1345
01:18:49,958 --> 01:18:51,152
- Why do you care?

1346
01:18:51,193 --> 01:18:54,321
- I care because
you're the reason I love math.

1347
01:18:54,362 --> 01:18:56,193
You taught me
numbers were everything.

1348
01:18:56,231 --> 01:18:57,528
And I noticed your numbers,

1349
01:18:57,566 --> 01:18:59,363
and I used to keep
a vertical bar graph

1350
01:18:59,401 --> 01:19:02,199
measuring them
against your moods.

1351
01:19:03,905 --> 01:19:06,430
- You made a graph?

1352
01:19:11,480 --> 01:19:13,175
Would you like to sit?

1353
01:19:15,317 --> 01:19:19,117
I left the store open,
